He would be drawn to Crassus by a certain congeniality of temper and taste, a man wh0, like himself, took delight in the thorough study of all the nobler products of human genius and especially of Greek art and knowledge, and who saw in such study the surest means of rising to eminence in oratory and statesmanship.
